 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P01-T071 (historical frequency + seasonality statistical baselines; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Seventy-first task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S6-P01). A complex model must first beat a cheap, interpretable baseline: fits a frequency (base rate) and a seasonality (month-of-year, Laplace-smoothed) baseline per prediction target from its settled history, with Brier/accuracy metrics, so every target has at least one reproducible baseline and no advanced model may be built for a target that has none. This is the FIRST statistical MODEL of the v0_1 cognition-system backtest layer; its formal spec is the in-evidence MODEL card arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T071/MODEL_baselines.md. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; the operational docs/governance/MODEL_SPEC.md and formula_registry.yaml (which track the deployed delivery system) are NOT touched -- operational model/formula/parameter registration is gated to cognition-layer promotion, consistent with every prior v0_1 tool; the production worker/cron/data are untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/baselines.py: frequency_baseline, seasonality_baseline (Laplace smoothing, unseen month -> smoothed global), brier_score / accuracy / evaluate, benchmark (fits baselines per target; has_reproducible_baseline only when the target has >= min_history labeled outcomes), may_develop_advanced (refuses advanced development for a target with no reproducible baseline). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T071/: MODEL_baselines.md, baselines_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T071/test-results/baselines_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): each target with history (G1 seasonal, G2 low base-rate) has a reproducible frequency + seasonality baseline with an in-range Brier and benchmark is byte-identical across runs; the frequency baseline equals the actual base rate, all probabilities are in [0,1], an unseen month falls back to the smoothed global rate, and on the seasonal target the seasonality baseline BEATS the base rate (Brier 0.083 < 0.266) -- a cheap baseline captures real signal; and a no-history target (G0) has no reproducible baseline and is refused advanced development, as are an absent target, an unknown target, and an empty-baselines entry. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P01-T070 (Dataset Snapshot + observed_at leakage guard; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Seventieth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S6-P01). Ensures 2026-backfilled old files cannot pretend to have been known at a historical point in time: a dataset snapshot is keyed on observed_at (when ADP actually fetched a document), never on doc_date (when the policy issued), so a 2016 policy observed only in 2026 is not in a 2018 snapshot. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only library, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/dataset_snapshot.py: snapshot(corpus, as_of) (docs with observed_at <= as_of, malformed/missing observed_at excluded, deterministic order + reproducible snapshot_id), assert_no_leakage(dataset, as_of) (raises LeakageError if any doc was observed after as_of or has an unverifiable observed_at -- the tripwire), and rebuild_for_prediction (reproduce the exact as-of dataset for a prediction's origin_date). Reuses T056 coverage_asof._parse_date. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T070/: dataset_snapshot_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T070/test-results/dataset_snapshot_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): a clean as-of snapshot passes the leakage guard, while EXTERNALLY injecting a future-observed doc, a 2026-backfilled doc, or a doc with no observed_at each RAISES (so injecting a future document makes the test fail); the snapshot is observed_at-keyed, not doc_date-keyed (a backfilled doc whose doc_date 2016-05-01 is before the 2018 as_of but whose observed_at is 2026-07-01 is excluded, so the 2018 snapshot is exactly [a, b]); and any prediction can rebuild its dataset (rebuild_for_prediction reproduces the snapshot_id, is order-independent and reproducible, and a later as_of expands the dataset). Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
